==English==

===Etymology===
From '''[[air]]''', plus '''[[bag]]'''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A protective system in [[automobile]]s in which when a crash occurs, a bag containing [[nitrogen]], formed by the [[explosive]] [[decomposition]] of [[sodium azide]], quickly [[inflate]]s in front of the [[driver]] or [[passenger]], preventing [[injury]] to the head. Side air bags, including the back seat passengers, also prevent injury.
#{{slang}}: A person who talks to much; a [[gossip]].

